{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*GOAL*

*As a…*user of the survey

*I want…*the Survey pages (landing, questions, and results) to be responsive and compatible with various devices 

*So that…*I can access and complete the survey seamlessly on any device
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*SCOPE*

*In scope:*

# Implementation of responsive design principles to adapt the layout and content of survey pages for optimal display on devices of varying screen sizes.
# Adjustment of page elements, such as text, images, and buttons, to maintain readability and usability across different devices.
# Testing of survey pages on different devices and screen resolutions to ensure consistent performance and functionality.
# Incorporation of navigation enhancements, such as touch-friendly controls and menu adjustments, for improved usability on mobile devices.



*Out of scope:*

* Redesigning the entire survey interface or making significant changes to the page layouts beyond responsiveness.
* Customization options specific to individual device types
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA*

*Given* I access the Survey pages on an iPad or mobile phone, 

*When* I view the landing page, questions page, and results page, 

*Then* I should observe that the layout and content adapt smoothly to the device screen size without distortion or overlap.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*TECH CONSIDERATIONS*
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*GOAL*

*As a…*user of the survey

*I want…*the AI Readiness Survey Pages to adhere to AND's design system

*So that…*I experience visual consistency and alignment with our brand identity throughout the surve
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*SCOPE*

*In scope:*

# Application of the company's color scheme, including primary, secondary, and accent colors, to the landing page interface.
# Implementation of typography guidelines, specifying font families, weights, and sizes for text elements throughout the page.
# Adherence to layout principles, such as spacing, grid systems, and element proportions, to ensure visual consistency and hierarchy.
# Integration of other visual elements, such as icons, imagery, and buttons, following the company's design system guidelines.



*Out of scope:*

* Creation of a new design system
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA*

*Given* I access the AI Readiness Survey Pages, 

*When* I view the page interface, 

*Then* I should see the company's design system applied consistently throughout the page elements.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*TECH CONSIDERATIONS*
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*GOAL*

*As a…*user that started the survey

*I want…*to be able to quit the survey in the middle and resume where I left off later

*So that…*I can complete the survey at my own pace without losing my progress or entered information
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*SCOPE*

*In scope:*

# Implementation of a mechanism for customers to pause the survey and resume at a later time.
# Storage of survey progress data in a persistent and retrievable format, such as database storage or local browser storage.



*Out of scope:*

* Integration of a "Save" button or feature within the survey interface
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA*

*Given* I decide to pause the survey and exit the page,
*When* I return to the survey at a later time,
*Then* I should see my previously entered information and progress retained.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*TECH CONSIDERATIONS*
{panel}

