*As a…*prospect client that just received a push email to answer the survey

*I want…*the Survey Landing Page URL to include the company name

*So that…*it enhances credibility and can be seamlessly embedded within our company website for future use.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*SCOPE*

*In scope:*

# Integration of the customised URL into the survey landing page interface. - and.digital
# Implementation of redirects or routing to ensure seamless navigation to the customised URL.



*Out of scope:*


{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA*

*Given* I am accessing the AI Readiness Survey Landing Page,
*When* I view the URL in the browser address bar,
*Then* I should see a customised URL that includes the company name.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*TECH CONSIDERATIONS*
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*GOAL*

*As a…*user that just completed the survey

*I want…*to see on the results page a personalised roadmap based on my survey responses

*So that…*I can understand the specific actions I need to take to improve my organisation's AI readiness.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*SCOPE*

*In scope:*

# Development of the Personalised Roadmap component to generate tailored recommendations based on survey responses. - content of the roadmap is provided per dimension and per stage
# Integration of the feature into the Results page interface.
# Design of the feature to provide clear and actionable next steps for customers to improve AI readiness.

According to designs attached.

*Out of scope:*

* 
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA*

*Given* I am on the Results page,
*When* I see the personalised roadmap,
*Then* I should see clear and actionable recommendations tailored to address identified strengths and areas for improvement in my organisation's AI readiness.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*TECH CONSIDERATIONS*
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*GOAL*

*As a…*user that just completed the survey

*I want…*to view my survey scoring in a graphic format on the Results page

*So that…*I can visually understand my performance across different dimensions of AI readiness
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*SCOPE*

*In scope:*

# Development of the Scoring Graphic Component to visually represent survey scoring - based on the results of the survey
# Integration of the component into the Results page interface.
# Design of the component to accurately reflect survey results across different dimensions of AI readiness.

According to the design attached.

*Out of scope:*

* 
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA*

*Given* I am on the Results page,
*When* I view the scoring graphic component,
*Then* I should see an accurate representation of my performance across different dimensions of AI readiness.
